sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as odh-notebook-controller
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Workbench as Workbench Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Workbench: Flow 1: User Creates Workbench
        User->>Dashboard: Select workbench type<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth
        Dashboard->>Controller: Create Notebook CR<br/>Kubernetes API
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/6443, ServiceAccount
        K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
        Registry-->>K8sAPI: Container image (digest-pinned)
        Note over K8sAPI: StatefulSet creates Pod<br/>with kube-rbac-proxy sidecar
        User->>Gateway: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>mTLS
        KRBAC->>KRBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>OAuth token validation
        KRBAC->>Workbench: Proxy to JupyterLab<br/>HTTP/8888
        Workbench-->>KRBAC: Notebook UI
        KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: JupyterLab UI
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over User,Runtime: Flow 2: Elyra Pipeline Submission
        User->>Workbench: Submit pipeline via Elyra<br/>HTTP/8888, Token
        Workbench->>KFP: Submit pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        KFP->>Registry: Pull runtime image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
        Registry-->>KFP: Runtime container image
        KFP->>Runtime: Execute pipeline step<br/>Container exec, ServiceAccount
        Runtime-->>KFP: Step output
        KFP-->>Workbench: Pipeline status
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Registry: Flow 3: Konflux Image Build
        participant GitHub as GitHub PR
        participant PaC as PipelinesAsCode
        participant Tekton as Tekton PipelineRun
        participant Quay as quay.io/opendatahub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

        GitHub->>PaC: Push/PR event<br/>HTTPS/443, Webhook
        PaC->>Tekton: Trigger PipelineRun<br/>CEL path filter
        Tekton->>GitHub: Clone repo<br/>HTTPS/443, git_auth_secret
        Tekton->>Registry: Pull base images<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
        Registry-->>Tekton: Base images (UBI9, CUDA, etc.)
        Tekton->>Tekton: buildah build<br/>(sandbox.py context)
        Tekton->>Quay: Push built image<br/>HTTPS/443, Push Secret
        Quay-->>Tekton: Image digest
    end
